<p>While most associate them today with amateurish 90s websites, animated GIFs continue to dance across screens around the world, turning up in surprising, subtle new variations that start to erode boundaries between <a href="http://iwdrm.tumblr.com/">cinema</a> and <a href="http://cinemagraphs.com/">digital photography</a>. The Stereogranimator joins these latter-day adventures of the venerable GIF, mashing up an important early genre of internet folk art with a nearly forgotten species of folk photography, the stereograph.</p>
